CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 30, 1944, pg. 11, reads: "The 1944 Crop of Courier Babies had males predominating, which bodes well for the future debbies. This handsome array of talent and charm and beauty all have Courier backgrounds, which may influence the future of the youngsters.  So, for a Christmas and New Year's gift to you....bottom row...Ira Vann Harris, son of Mr. and Mrs. Charles (Teenie) Harris (Courier staff photographer)... - Courier photos by Harris and Sockwell."
TitMainTitle: Ira Vann Harris seated in high chair with shark printed on cushion, in interior with two toned door in background
